package main

import (
	"encoding/csv"
	"encoding/json"
	"fmt"
	"io/ioutil"
	"log"
	"os"
	"regexp"
	"sort"
	"strconv"
	"strings"
	"time"
)

// UIMessage represents a message from Cline's UI messages JSON
type UIMessage struct {
	TS   int64  `json:"ts"`
	Type string `json:"type"`
	Say  string `json:"say,omitempty"`
	Text string `json:"text,omitempty"`
}

// APIRequestData represents the parsed API request data from UI messages
type APIRequestData struct {
	Request     string  `json:"request"`
	Cost        float64 `json:"cost"`
	TokensIn    int     `json:"tokensIn"`
	TokensOut   int     `json:"tokensOut"`
	CacheWrites int     `json:"cacheWrites"`
	CacheReads  int     `json:"cacheReads"`
}

// CostEntry represents a single cost tracking entry
type CostEntry struct {
	RequestSummary         string
	AskSay                 string
	Text                   string
	RequestCost            float64
	Timestamp              string
	ContextTokensUsed      int
	TotalCost              float64
	UserRequest            string
	ClineAction            string
	ToolUsed               string
	HasImages              string
	Phase                  string
	ContextPercentage      string
	SearchTermInTranscript string
	CostNotes              string
	TimeApprox             string
}

func main() {
	if len(os.Args) != 3 {
		log.Fatal("Usage: cost_extractor <ui_messages.json> <output.csv>")
	}

	uiMessagesFile := os.Args[1]
	csvFile := os.Args[2]

	// Read and parse ui_messages.json
	data, err := ioutil.ReadFile(uiMessagesFile)
	if err != nil {
		log.Fatalf("‚ùå Error reading ui_messages.json: %v", err)
	}

	var messages []UIMessage
	if err := json.Unmarshal(data, &messages); err != nil {
		log.Fatalf("‚ùå Error parsing JSON: %v", err)
	}

	// Extract API costs and build context from user messages
	var apiCosts []CostEntry
	var totalCost float64
	requestCounter := 1

	// Build a map of user messages for context
	userMessages := make(map[int64]string)
	clineResponses := make(map[int64]string)

	// Build a map of different types of user interactions
	var mainUserRequest string
	var userFeedbacks []string

	for _, msg := range messages {
		if msg.Type == "say" && msg.Say == "text" && msg.Text != "" {
			// This is the actual user request that started the task
			if mainUserRequest == "" {
				mainUserRequest = msg.Text
			}
		} else if msg.Type == "say" && msg.Say == "user_feedback" && msg.Text != "" {
			// Collect user feedback messages
			userFeedbacks = append(userFeedbacks, msg.Text)
		} else if msg.Type == "ask" && msg.Text != "" {
			// Extract the actual user request text (not lowercased, preserve original)
			userText := msg.Text
			// Keep more context but clean it up
			if len(userText) > 200 {
				userText = userText[:200] + "..."
			}
			// Clean up newlines and extra spaces
			userText = strings.ReplaceAll(userText, "\n", " ")
			userText = strings.ReplaceAll(userText, "\t", " ")
			// Remove multiple spaces
			userText = regexp.MustCompile(`\s+`).ReplaceAllString(userText, " ")
			userText = strings.TrimSpace(userText)
			userMessages[msg.TS] = userText
		} else if msg.Type == "say" && msg.Say == "text" && msg.Text != "" {
			// Extract Cline's responses for determining what Cline actually did
			responseText := msg.Text
			if len(responseText) > 150 {
				responseText = responseText[:150] + "..."
			}
			clineResponses[msg.TS] = responseText
		}
	}

	// Process all messages to create entries with new structure
	isFirstEntry := true
	for _, msg := range messages {
		timestamp := time.Unix(msg.TS/1000, (msg.TS%1000)*1000000)

		var entry CostEntry
		entry.Timestamp = timestamp.Format("2006-01-02 15:04:05")
		entry.TimeApprox = timestamp.Format("15:04")
		entry.ContextTokensUsed = 0
		entry.RequestCost = 0.0
		entry.TotalCost = totalCost
		entry.HasImages = "No"
		entry.Phase = "User Input"
		entry.ContextPercentage = "0%"
		entry.CostNotes = "User feedback message"
		entry.SearchTermInTranscript = "user_feedback"

		// Handle different message types
		if msg.Type == "say" && msg.Say == "text" && msg.Text != "" && isFirstEntry {
			// First entry - main user request
			entry.RequestSummary = "Task Request: " + msg.Text
			entry.AskSay = `"say": "text"`
			entry.Text = msg.Text
			entry.ClineAction = "Task Description"
			entry.ToolUsed = "N/A"
			isFirstEntry = false
			apiCosts = append(apiCosts, entry)
			requestCounter++
		} else if msg.Type == "say" && msg.Say == "user_feedback" && msg.Text != "" {
			// User feedback entries
			entry.RequestSummary = "User Input: " + msg.Text
			entry.AskSay = `"say": "user_feedback"`
			entry.Text = msg.Text
			entry.ClineAction = "User Feedback"
			entry.ToolUsed = "N/A"
			apiCosts = append(apiCosts, entry)
			requestCounter++
		} else if msg.Type == "say" && msg.Say == "api_req_started" && msg.Text != "" {
			// API request entries
			var apiData APIRequestData
			if err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(msg.Text), &apiData); err == nil {
				totalCost += apiData.Cost
				entry.RequestSummary = "API Request: " + apiData.Request[:min(50, len(apiData.Request))] + "..."
				entry.AskSay = `"say": "api_req_started"`
				entry.Text = msg.Text
				entry.RequestCost = apiData.Cost
				entry.TotalCost = totalCost
				entry.ContextTokensUsed = apiData.TokensIn + apiData.TokensOut
				entry.ClineAction = "API request started"
				entry.ToolUsed = "API Request"
				entry.Phase = "Completion"
				entry.SearchTermInTranscript = "api_request"
				entry.CostNotes = "ACTUAL cost from Cline interface"
				apiCosts = append(apiCosts, entry)
				requestCounter++
			}
		} else if msg.Type == "ask" && msg.Text != "" {
			// Tool usage entries
			entry.RequestSummary = ""
			entry.AskSay = `"ask": "tool"`
			entry.Text = msg.Text
			entry.ClineAction = "Tool operation"
			entry.ToolUsed = "ask operation"
			entry.Phase = "Exploration"
			entry.SearchTermInTranscript = "ask"
			apiCosts = append(apiCosts, entry)
			requestCounter++
		}
	}

	if len(apiCosts) == 0 {
		fmt.Println("‚ö†Ô∏è  No API costs found in ui_messages.json")
		return
	}

	// Sort all entries by timestamp chronologically
	sort.Slice(apiCosts, func(i, j int) bool {
		timeI, errI := time.Parse("2006-01-02 15:04:05", apiCosts[i].Timestamp)
		timeJ, errJ := time.Parse("2006-01-02 15:04:05", apiCosts[j].Timestamp)
		if errI != nil || errJ != nil {
			return false
		}
		return timeI.Before(timeJ)
	})

	// Calculate context percentages
	maxTokens := 0
	for _, cost := range apiCosts {
		if cost.ContextTokensUsed > maxTokens {
			maxTokens = cost.ContextTokensUsed
		}
	}

	for i := range apiCosts {
		if maxTokens > 0 {
			percentage := int((float64(apiCosts[i].ContextTokensUsed) / float64(maxTokens)) * 100)
			apiCosts[i].ContextPercentage = fmt.Sprintf("%d%%", percentage)
		} else {
			apiCosts[i].ContextPercentage = "0%"
		}
	}

	// Write to CSV file
	file, err := os.Create(csvFile)
	if err != nil {
		log.Fatalf("‚ùå Error creating CSV file: %v", err)
	}
	defer file.Close()

	writer := csv.NewWriter(file)
	defer writer.Flush()

	// Write header with new structure: Request Summary, Ask/Say, Cost, Text, Timestamp, Context tokens used, Total cost, [existing columns]
	header := []string{
		"Request Summary", "Ask/Say", "Cost", "Text", "Timestamp", "Context tokens used", "Total cost",
		"User_Request", "Cline_Action", "Tool_Used", "Has_Images", "Phase", "Context_Percentage",
		"Search_Term_In_Transcript", "Cost_Notes", "Time_Approx",
	}
	if err := writer.Write(header); err != nil {
		log.Fatalf("‚ùå Error writing CSV header: %v", err)
	}

	// Write entries with new structure
	for _, entry := range apiCosts {
		record := []string{
			entry.RequestSummary,
			entry.AskSay,
			entry.Text,
			fmt.Sprintf("%.6f", entry.RequestCost),
			entry.Timestamp,
			strconv.Itoa(entry.ContextTokensUsed),
			fmt.Sprintf("%.6f", entry.TotalCost),
			entry.UserRequest,
			entry.ClineAction,
			entry.ToolUsed,
			entry.HasImages,
			entry.Phase,
			entry.ContextPercentage,
			entry.SearchTermInTranscript,
			entry.CostNotes,
			entry.TimeApprox,
		}
		if err := writer.Write(record); err != nil {
			log.Fatalf("‚ùå Error writing CSV record: %v", err)
		}
	}

	fmt.Printf("‚úÖ Successfully updated %s with %d cost entries\n", csvFile, len(apiCosts))
	fmt.Printf("üí∞ Total cost for this task: $%.6f\n", totalCost)
}

// Helper functions
func isCommonWord(word string) bool {
	commonWords := map[string]bool{
		"the": true, "and": true, "for": true, "are": true, "but": true, "not": true,
		"you": true, "all": true, "can": true, "had": true, "her": true, "was": true,
		"one": true, "our": true, "out": true, "day": true, "get": true, "has": true,
		"him": true, "his": true, "how": true, "man": true, "new": true, "now": true,
		"old": true, "see": true, "two": true, "way": true, "who": true, "boy": true,
		"did": true, "its": true, "let": true, "put": true, "say": true, "she": true,
		"too": true, "use": true, "want": true, "with": true, "this": true, "that": true,
	}
	return commonWords[strings.ToLower(word)]
}

func min(a, b int) int {
	if a < b {
		return a
	}
	return b
}
